{# Coded Language Decoder - What they said vs what they meant #}
<div class="decoder">
  <div class="decoder__intro">
    <p>
      <strong>How to read this:</strong> After explicit racism became politically unacceptable,
      strategists developed code words that communicated racial messages while maintaining
      "plausible deniability." Lee Atwater explained this evolution in his 1981 interview.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="decoder__grid">
    {% for item in codedLanguage %}
    <article class="decoder__card">
      <header class="decoder__card-header">
        <h4 class="decoder__term">"{{ item.term }}"</h4>
        <span class="decoder__usage">{{ item.usage }}</span>
      </header>
      <div class="decoder__meaning">
        <span class="decoder__label">Actually means:</span>
        <p>{{ item.meaning }}</p>
      </div>
      <div class="decoder__example">
        <span class="decoder__label">Example:</span>
        <p>{{ item.example }}</p>
      </div>
      <footer class="decoder__note">
        {{ item.note }}
      </footer>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>
